    "justification": "Two conjuncts: (1) |delta AUROC| < 0.02 means biophysics adds essentially nothing on top of the age+length+class baseline — the desired NULL behavior for the designed negative control; (2) baseline AUROC > 0.5 ensures the test is real (the baseline can predict H3K9me3 above chance) so the null delta is informative rather than a degenerate failure case. The conclusion licenses 'biophysics is NOT involved in H3K9me3 silencing recruitment in H1 ESC' as an outcome of POSITIVE register: the claim that the negative control behaves negatively is supported.",
    "failure_mode": "If |delta AUROC| > 0.02, the negative control would be contaminated and the bivalent / H3K27me3 / quiescent positive results would lose the credibility lift this control provides. Observed delta = +0.004 is well within the null band."
  },
  "conclusion": {
    "assertion": "In H1 embryonic stem cells (E003), DNA biophysical features add essentially nothing to baseline (age + length + class) for predicting H3K9me3 chromatin state on transposable elements (delta AUROC = +0.004). This is the designed negative control: H3K9me3 silencing is recruited by KRAB-ZnF sequence-motif recognition, not biophysical properties; the null delta confirms the experiment design is selective rather than measuring 'biophysics predicts everything.'",
